<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A110926379BF923C712F8FE" pageId="1" pageNumber="423" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A110926379BF923C712F8FE" blockId="1.[151,1436,1747,1990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A110926379BF923C74AF925" bold="true" box="[151,274,1747,1773]" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingRegion id="F87FF8670A1109263588F923C4B9F925" box="[644,737,1747,1773]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="42AC76150A11092635E7F923C569F925" box="[747,817,1747,1773]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">China</collectingCountry>
, and the illustrations of male genitalia were provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E2A4B740A110926379BF907C71BF8D9" author="Li, Z. Z. &amp; Dai, R. H. &amp; Xing, J. C." box="[151,323,1783,1810]" pageId="1" pageNumber="423" refId="ref4322" refString="Li, Z. Z., Dai, R. H. &amp; Xing, J. C. (2011) Deltocephalinae from China (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Popular Science Press, Beijing, 336 pp. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="book" year="2011">
Li 
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A11092637BBF908C6B0F8D9" box="[183,232,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A11092636FEF908C424F8D9" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" box="[498,636,1783,1809]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A11092636FEF908C424F8D9" box="[498,636,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="423">P. productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may be distinguished from the latter by the forewing with irregular black markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
